    {
      "id": "PopularPost303131",
      "post_content": "There are a lot better cards to combo with [Underworld Dreams](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Underworld Dreams) - things like [Spiteful Visions](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Spiteful Visions) which would have you going black/red or blue/black/red, not white/black.  \n  \nThat said, this card isn't terrible. Yes, you would be better off splashing blue or really any color if you wanted card draw in your white deck, but casual players don't always want to change the colors of their decks to open up their card options, a fact which is especially true in Commander as changing the colors would mean changing the commander chosen as well. This type of effect is exactly the type of card draw I would expect white to get. I just wish white got more of the [Vision Skeins](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vision Skeins) type effects than blue does, as blue has enough other card draw mechanics available that it doesn't need these too.",
      "posted_by": "sarroth",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost303131\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">There are a lot better cards to combo with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Underworld Dreams\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Underworld Dreams\">Underworld Dreams</a> - things like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Spiteful Visions\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Spiteful Visions\">Spiteful Visions</a> which would have you going black/red or blue/black/red, not white/black.<br/><br/>That said, this card isn't terrible. Yes, you would be better off splashing blue or really any color if you wanted card draw in your white deck, but casual players don't always want to change the colors of their decks to open up their card options, a fact which is especially true in Commander as changing the colors would mean changing the commander chosen as well.  This type of effect is exactly the type of card draw I would expect white to get. I just wish white got more of the <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Vision Skeins\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vision Skeins\">Vision Skeins</a> type effects than blue does, as blue has enough other card draw mechanics available that it doesn't need these too.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '303131'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy20957\">sarroth</span>\r\n                                (3/7/2013 5:55:15 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>"
    },
    {
      "id": "PopularPost317247",
      "post_content": "If you are playing mono-white EDH/Commander, then this card is good.  \n  \nMono-white has the distinct disadvantage of having almost nothing in the way of card draw. You try to get ahead in the early game and stay ahead, but without cards in the midgame you start to fall off.  \n  \nThat's where cards like Howling Mine, Mikokoro, and Truce come in handy. You get to refill your hand at instant speed, and because of the way mono-white works, you need cards more than your opponents need cards. If you are worried about them gaining too much card advantage, then run Rule of Law and/or Curse of Exhaustion, which you should be doing anyways to stop combo players.  \n  \nOverall, a situational card, but not a bad card by any means.",
      "posted_by": "snazzycool",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost317247\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_post\">If you are playing mono-white EDH/Commander, then this card is good.<br/><br/>Mono-white has the distinct disadvantage of having almost nothing in the way of card draw. You try to get ahead in the early game and stay ahead, but without cards in the midgame you start to fall off.<br/><br/>That's where cards like Howling Mine, Mikokoro, and Truce come in handy. You get to refill your hand at instant speed, and because of the way mono-white works, you need cards more than your opponents need cards. If you are worried about them gaining too much card advantage, then run Rule of Law and/or Curse of Exhaustion, which you should be doing anyways to stop combo players.<br/><br/>Overall, a situational card, but not a bad card by any means.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '317247'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy88189\">snazzycool</span>\r\n                                (5/22/2013 6:47:35 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\"